CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 12, 1946, pg. 8 reads: " "YW" Scene Of Wedding - The YWCA was the scene of a fashionable wedding of late summer, when Miss Delores Gayton, daughter of Mrs. Sarah H. Gayton of Bethoven Street, became the bride of Walter Charlton, son of Mr. and Mrs. George Charlton of Reed Street, [the] Rev. S. Williams performed the ceremony. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Walter Herman Charlton and Dolores Gayton Charlton, cutting two tiered wedding cake, in YMCA
